17 Existing law requires such special assessments to be deposited with the State
18 Treasurer for credit to the Water District Account to be accounted for in basin well
19 accounts. (NRS 534.040) Section 3 requires the State Engineer to provide, not
20 more than once each year and upon the written request of a board of county
21 commissioners that levies a special assessment or appropriates money from the
22 general fund of the county, a report on the expenditures and activities from the
23 Water District Account for the particular basin well account of that groundwater
24 basin. Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming change to account for the
25 renumbering of provisions in section 3.
26 Existing law further establishes, subject to certain exceptions, a minimum
27 charge of $1 for a special assessment upon certain areas in which the use of
28 groundwater is predominantly for agricultural purposes. (NRS 534.040) Section 3:
29 (1) removes the minimum charge; and (2) establishes a maximum charge that is
30 equal to the existing charge as of June 30, 2025, plus the annual percentage
31 increase in the Consumer Price Index for the immediately preceding year for such
32 assessments. Section 3 further authorizes the State Engineer to increase the amount
33 of the maximum charge with the approval of the board of county commissioners.
34 Section 4 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Division of Water
35 Resources of the State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources for: (1)
36 costs associated with updates to the water budgets of the groundwater basins in this
37 State; (2) the collection of data and the monitoring of water resources and
38 ecosystems in this State; (3) the digitization of records and data of the Division; and
39 (4) hiring staff for the adjudication of vested water rights in the groundwater basins
40 in this State.
